          "description": "You can't be charmed or frightened while raging. If charmed or frightened when you rage, the effect is suspended for the duration.",
          "level": 6,
          "name": "Mindless Rage",
          "source": "subclass",
        },
        {
          "description": "You have advantage on initiative rolls. If surprised at the start of combat, you can still act normally on your first turn if you enter your rage before doing anything else.",
          "level": 7,
          "name": "Feral Instinct",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "You can roll one additional weapon damage die on a critical hit with a melee attack. Two extra dice at level 13, three at level 17.",
          "level": 9,
          "name": "Brutal Critical",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "As an action, frighten one creature within 30 ft that can see and hear you. It must succeed on a Wisdom save (DC 8 + proficiency + Charisma modifier) or be frightened until the end of your next turn. On a success, the target is immune to this feature for 24 hours.",
          "level": 10,
          "name": "Intimidating Presence",
          "source": "subclass",
        },
        {
          "description": "When reduced to 0 HP while raging without dying outright, make a DC 10 Con save (DC +5 each use; resets on a short or long rest) to drop to 1 HP instead.",
          "level": 11,
          "name": "Relentless Rage",
          "source": "class",
        },
      ],
      "resources": [
        {
          "description": "Bonus action: enter a rage for up to 1 minute (ends early if you fall unconscious or choose to end it). Resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage (applied automatically) and advantage on Strength checks & saves while raging. Regain all rages on a long rest.",
          "key": "rage",
          "label": "Rage",
          "recharge": "longRest",
          "total": 5,
        },
      ],
    },
    "level": 12,
  },
  {
    "info": {
      "features": [
        {
          "description": "As a bonus action, enter a rage lasting up to 1 minute. You gain advantage on Strength checks and saves, a bonus to melee damage (+2 at L1; +3 at L9; +4 at L16), and resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage. You can't cast or concentrate on spells while raging.",
          "level": 1,
          "name": "Rage",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "While not wearing armor, your AC equals 10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Constitution modifier. You may use a shield.",
          "level": 1,
          "name": "Unarmored Defense",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "You have advantage on Dexterity saving throws against effects that you can see, such as traps and spells. Doesn't apply when blinded, deafened, or incapacitated.",
          "level": 2,
          "name": "Danger Sense",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "When making your first attack on your turn, you may attack recklessly: you have advantage on melee weapon attack rolls using Strength this turn, but attack rolls against you also have advantage until your next turn.",
          "level": 2,
          "name": "Reckless Attack",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "When you rage, choose to go into a frenzy. For the rage's duration, make one melee weapon attack as a bonus action on each of your turns. When the rage ends, you suffer one level of exhaustion.",
          "level": 3,
          "name": "Frenzy",
          "source": "subclass",
        },
        {
          "description": "You can attack twice whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.",
          "level": 5,
          "name": "Extra Attack",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "Your speed increases by 10 feet while you aren't wearing heavy armor.",
          "level": 5,
          "name": "Fast Movement",
          "source": "class",
        },
        {
          "description": "You can't be charmed or frightened while raging. If charmed or frightened when you rage, the effect is suspended for the duration.",
